    "finalTextLength": 1146,
    "finalText": "AP is clean in volume, but bad in age.\n\n**Right now: $14,110 outstanding total, and 100% of it is in 90+ days past due.** There’s nothing sitting in current, 1–30, 31–60, or 61–90.\n\n### Aging snapshot\n- **Current:** $0\n- **1–30 days:** $0\n- **31–60 days:** $0\n- **61–90 days:** $0\n- **90+ days:** **$14,110** across **2 bills**\n\n### What that means\nThe balance is small, so this is **not a cash-volume problem**. It **is** a cleanup problem.\n\nWhen every open AP dollar is 90+ days old, one of two things is usually true:\n- the bills are being ignored, or\n- they’re in dispute and never got resolved properly.\n\nEither way, it’s the kind of thing that creates unnecessary vendor friction.\n\n### What I’d do next\n1. **Identify the 2 bills today** — vendor, invoice date, amount, and whether they’re disputed or simply unpaid.\n2. **Clear or resolve them this week.**\n3. **Check if either vendor is active on a current project** so this doesn’t turn into a field relationship issue over a relatively small balance.\n\nIf you want, I can pull the **recent AP bills** or **vendor spend detail** next and tell you exactly which vendors make up that $14,110."
