        "analysis": "## AP Aging Snapshot — Right Now\n\n**Total outstanding AP is $14,110, and every dollar of it is over 90 days past due.** There is no current or 1–90 day balance showing in the live Acumatica aging report. [Source: Acumatica AP Aging - as of 2026-05-02T10:41:52.932Z]\n\n### Aging buckets\n| Aging Bucket | Balance | Bill Count | Status |\n|---|---:|---:|---|\n| Current | $0 | 0 | Clear |\n| 1–30 Days | $0 | 0 | Clear |\n| 31–60 Days | $0 | 0 | Clear |\n| 61–90 Days | $0 | 0 | Clear |\n| 90+ Days | **$14,110** | **2** | **Critical** |\n\n[Source: Acumatica AP Aging - as of 2026-05-02T10:41:52.932Z]\n\n### What this means\n- **100% of AP is overdue beyond 90 days.** That is the only concentration in the report. [Source: Acumatica AP Aging - as of 2026-05-02T10:41:52.932Z]\n- The report shows **2 bills** in the 90+ bucket, but it does **not** identify the vendors or bill-level details. So I can confirm the aging risk, but not yet name the counterparties from this data alone. [Source: Acumatica AP Aging - as of 2026-05-02T10:41:52.932Z]\n\n### Risk read\n- This is a **critical overdue payable concentration** because the entire AP balance is stuck in the oldest aging bucket.\n- The main risk is **vendor friction / collection pressure**: even though the balance is not large in absolute terms, bills that are 90+ days past due are the most likely to trigger follow-up, service interruption, or strained vendor terms.\n\n### Recommended actions\n1. **Identify the 2 past-due bills immediately** and confirm which vendors they belong to.  \n2. **Prioritize payment or dispute resolution this week** — this aging profile is already deep into critical territory.  \n3. **Check whether these bills are tied to any active project commitments** so we can see if the unpaid balance is creating field risk or delivery risk.\n\nIf you want, I can next pull **recent bills** or a **vendor spend report** to identify exactly which vendors make up the $14,110.",
